subSubSection.paragraph:
Cell V oval, half or a third of the length of cell IV, not connected with cell III, distinctively paler than its surroundings. Outer appendage unbranched. Inner appendage consisting of a small basal cell supporting short branches terminated by few antheridia in young thalli, but proliferating into some variably elongated sterile branches when ageing. [Detailed description: 
Santamaria 1998
]
